Golden DEK wrap sample
======================

`golden-dek-wrapped.bin` is a **util header** (16 bytes) plus an **openssl enc**
payload produced with **recipe 01** parameters and the fixed smoke inputs from
`../dek-wrap-test-vectors.bash` (`SMOKE_PASSPHRASE`, `SMOKE_PLAINTEXT`).

The salt is embedded in the openssl blob, so this file is **fixed** for CI and
regression checks. Regenerate when recipe crypto parameters **or** those test
vectors change:

```bash
cd keyring/testdata
bash ./regen-golden-dek-wrap.sh
```

Run the verifier (from anywhere):

```bash
bash keyring/testdata/verify-dek-wrap-golden.sh
```
